The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 15 March is 241,042 (27,781.5 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 10 March, there were 7,055 new confirmed cases (813.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 03 March, there were 4,283 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 65% (2,772 extra cases).
